TY  - JOUR
AU  - Krishna, Pravin
T1  - Regionalism and Multilateralism: A Political Economy Approach*
PY  - 1998
Y1  - 1998/02/01
DO  - 10.1162/00335539851144162
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 113
IS  - 1
SP  - 227
EP  - 251
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Preferential trading arrangements are analyzed from the viewpoint of the “new political economy” that views trade policy as being determined by lobbying of concentrated interest groups. Two conclusions are reached: first, that trade-diverting preferential arrangements are more likely to be supported politically; and second, that such preferential arrangements could critically change domestic incentives so multilateral liberalization that is initially politically feasible could be rendered infeasible by a preferential arrangement. The larger the trade diversion resulting from the preferential arrangement, the more likely this will be the case.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/00335539851144162
ER  - 



